WEBVTT

00:00,000 --> 00:02,950
A practical leadership workflow for data and analytics that teams will use 03040530 sounds strategic, but the real constraint is operating behavior in the workflow.

00:03,000 --> 00:05,950
Because practical is easier to produce now, teams can mistake volume for progress. Last week in the weekly operations standup, the blocker was not motivation.

00:06,000 --> 00:08,950
Problem one: volume around practical grows faster than attention and adoption.

00:09,000 --> 00:11,950
So start with one owner, one metric, and one weekly review loop before scaling.

00:12,000 --> 00:14,950
Then scale only after one-week evidence shows real movement.

00:15,000 --> 00:17,950
Problem two: teams drift when analytics expectations change faster than coaching adapts.

00:18,000 --> 00:20,950
So the real test is simple: does this change operating behavior in live projects?

00:21,000 --> 00:29,950
What do you think?
